den|authorlink=Anthony Holden|title=King Charles III: A Biography|publisher=Grove|year=1988|isbn=978-1-55584-309-0|url=https://archive.org/details/kingcharlesiiibi00hold}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Anthony|last=Holden|title=Charles at Fifty|publisher=Random House|year=1998|isbn=978-0-375-50175-3|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/charlesatfifty00hold}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Holden |first=Anthony|title=Charles: A Biography |publisher=Corgi Books |year=1999 |isbn=978-0-552-99744-7}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Charles|last=Jencks|authorlink=Charles Jencks|title=Prince, Architects & New Wave Monarchy|publisher=Rizzoli|year=1988|isbn=978-0-8478-1010-9|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/princearchitects0000jenc}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Junor|first=Penny|title=Charles: Victim or Villain?|publisher=Harpercollins|year=1998|isbn=978-0-00-255900-3|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/charlesvictimorv0000juno}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Peter|last=Lane|title=Prince Charles:a study in development|publisher=Robert Hale|year=1988|isbn=978-0-7090-3320-2}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Douglas|last=Liversidge|title=Prince Charles: monarch in the making |publisher=A. Barker|year=1975}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Christopher|last=Martin|title=Prince Charles and the Architectural Debate (Architectural Design Profile)|publisher=St Martin's Press |year=1990|isbn=978-0-312-04048-2}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Jean|last=Nugent|title=Prince Charles, England's Future King|publisher=Dillon|year=1982|isbn=978-0-87518-226-1}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Simon|last=Regan|authorlink=Simon Regan|title=Charles, the clown prince|publisher=Everest Books |year=1977|isbn=978-0-905018-50-8}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Joan M.|last=Veon|title=Prince Charles: The Sustainable Prince|publisher=Hearthstone|year=1997|isbn=978-1-57558-021-0}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Geoffrey|last=Wakeford|title=Charles, Prince of Wales|publisher=Associated Newspapers|year=1962}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Catherine|last=Mayer|tit